{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eb075f62-0d46-4702-a250-cc0d0a59beee","content":"To migrate your NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update packages in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"...\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"4.6.0\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"5.0.0\" /> <!-- or later -->\n```\n\nNUnit3TestAdapter 5.0+ includes Microsoft.Testing.Platform support and replaces the need for `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`.\n\n**2. Enable the new platform in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. (Optional) Add a `Program.cs` entry point** if you want to run your test project as an executable directly (not required for `dotnet test`):\n\n```csharp\nusing NUnit.Testing.Platform;\nNUnitTestingPlatform.EntryPoint(args);\n```\n\n**4. Run tests** the same way:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- .NET 8+ is required for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n- The `--` separator is used for platform-specific options: `dotnet test -- --help`.\n- Some VSTest `.runsettings` options may need adjustment or have new equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"62f7b2b7-792b-440e-9ecf-e4b474cbfaf3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to look at any files.","outputTokens":428,"requestId":"E3D9:3FC1BD:15B9980:1854CC0:6A051F9B"},"id":"3b9a7961-2122-45d9-a065-5c43555b3b6c","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:04:37.390Z","parentId":"f012f6e3-cfc5-48e1-baf8-03bbff37ce2b"}
